The paper deals with the design of a new protocol for slotted ALOHA over erasure channels using polar coding. This involves the use of coding theory and information theory concepts, which are typically covered in the cs.IT (Information Theory) sub-category. The protocol is designed for wireless networks, which falls under the cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture) sub-category. The paper also involves the development of decoding algorithms, which could be categorized under cs.SI (Signal Processing) or cs.SY (Systems and Control). Finally, the paper deals with the analysis of throughput bounds, which could be categorized under cs.COM (Computational Complexity).
